my airline app's giving
me real-time flight info,

00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:04.680
my weather apps, Uber, et cetera.

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:05.670
But while we're up here

00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:07.950
talking about the screen on
this phone, it's also brighter,

00:03:07.950 --> 00:03:11.730
It's up to 2,000 knits now,
which looks awesome outdoors.

00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:15.450
But also, it's 2023,

00:03:15.450 --> 00:03:20.450
and this is an $800 phone that
still has a 60 hertz display.

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:24.870
This is actually really fascinating to me.

00:03:24.870 --> 00:03:25.710
It's so odd.

00:03:25.710 --> 00:03:26.543
Like, on one hand,

00:03:26.543 --> 00:03:28.950
for most people buying this
phone, it's totally fine.

00:03:28.950 --> 00:03:31.620
It literally doesn't have,
it's a new baseline iPhone,

00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:35.940
have you talked to someone who
buys a new baseline iPhone?

00:03:35.940 --> 00:03:36.960
They literally don't care.

00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:37.950
It doesn't matter,

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:39.240
it's not something they pay attention to,

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:40.080
you could ask them right now

00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:41.790
how many frames per second their phone is

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:43.950
and they wouldn't have an
answer, just doesn't matter.

00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:45.000
So just as long as it works

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:47.310
and it's all relatively
smooth like last year

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:49.140
and the year before and the year before,

00:03:49.140 --> 00:03:51.120
it's totally a non-factor.

00:03:51.120 --> 00:03:54.750
I have actually literally
handed 120 hertz phone to people

00:03:54.750 --> 00:03:56.760
next to a 60 hertz phone,

00:03:56.760 --> 00:03:59.010
and even side by side next to each other,

00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:00.480
they can't see the difference.

00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:01.950
Or if they do, it's just like,

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:04.200
oh, that's a subtle thing
that seems kind of neat

00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:06.270
but they'd be totally
fine missing out on it.

00:04:06.270 --> 00:04:07.830
So with the target
demographic of this phone,

00:04:07.830 --> 00:04:08.730
it's totally fine.

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:13.230
But on the other hand, Apple,

00:04:13.230 --> 00:04:16.770
the richest technology
company in the world,

00:04:16.770 --> 00:04:19.560
does stuff all the time

00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:22.500
that regular people will
literally never notice,

00:04:22.500 --> 00:04:25.290
that are subtle improvements
or changes here and there,

00:04:25.290 --> 00:04:26.123
all the time.

00:04:26.123 --> 00:04:27.870
Like, when they switched
these baseline iPhones

00:04:27.870 --> 00:04:30.300
from LCD to OLED displays,

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:32.490
do you think any of these
people actually noticed that?

00:04:32.490 --> 00:04:34.710
Or what about going from
the A15 Bionic last year

00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:36.150
to this A16 Bionic?

00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:38.310
Do you think people are actually noticing

00:04:38.310 --> 00:04:39.210
the differences here?

00:04:39.210 --> 00:04:42.150
Or what about when they
just added 5G to the iPhone

00:04:42.150 --> 00:04:44.340
and most people didn't care?

00:04:44.340 --> 00:04:46.740
Like, making subtle improvements over time

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:49.440
is what modern smartphones
are all about these days.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:50.670
And I would actually argue that

00:04:50.670 --> 00:04:52.800
a higher refresh rate is more noticeable

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:55.680
to more people than some
of those other things.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:58.740
Like, I think you could today
hand me, a professional,

00:04:58.740 --> 00:05:02.820
an unlabeled iPhone with an
A15 Bionic and an A16 Bionic,

00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:04.860
and it would take me quite some time

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:07.260
to find the real differences between them.

00:05:07.260 --> 00:05:08.820
And so, that combined with the fact

00:05:08.820 --> 00:05:12.180
that it's incredibly cheap
and easy and reasonable

00:05:12.180 --> 00:05:14.610
to get to like at least a 90 hertz phone,

00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:19.117
isn't the new Moto G is
like 90 hertz at $170

00:05:20.310 --> 00:05:21.150
or something like that?

00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:22.890
Now I'm sure that's a
horrible looking screen

00:05:22.890 --> 00:05:23.970
compared to this iPhone,

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:27.660
it's 720P with the brightness
of a box of crayons.

00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:31.170
But still they decided
to add that to that phone

00:05:31.170 --> 00:05:33.750
because Motorola knew that
enough people would notice it

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:36.420
and feel that smoothness difference

00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:39.330
and it's a higher level
of perceived performance.

00:05:39.330 --> 00:05:40.380
So it's just wild to me,

00:05:40.380 --> 00:05:43.290
knowing how easy it would
be for Apple to make this

00:05:43.290 --> 00:05:47.070
even a 90 hertz display, but
they just refuse to do it

00:05:47.070 --> 00:05:50.730
because they've attached the
word Pro to that feature.

00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:53.670
It's promotion for the Pro phones.

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:55.320
And it just strikes me as a tool

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:58.050
just to sort of continue widening the gap

00:05:58.050 --> 00:06:00.570
as much as they can
between the Pro iPhones

00:06:00.570 --> 00:06:03.060
and the non-Pro iPhones,
and they're happy to do it,

00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:05.460
even if it makes this iPhone 15

00:06:05.460 --> 00:06:08.160
the most expensive phone in the world

00:06:08.160 --> 00:06:09.480
with a 60 hertz display.

00:06:09.480 --> 00:06:11.760
Anyway, speaking of widening that gap,

00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:15.690
the Pro phones this year also
got a brand new A17 Pro chip

00:06:15.690 --> 00:06:19.530
but this iPhone 15 gets
last year's A16 Bionic

00:06:19.530 --> 00:06:20.460
from the 14 Pro.

00:06:20.460 --> 00:06:22.230
Honestly, the renaming of the Pro chip

00:06:22.230 --> 00:06:23.460
might be the most interesting part

00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:24.900
because it implies that

00:06:24.900 --> 00:06:27.480
it's definitely not going to trickle down

00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:29.760
to the baseline phone next year.

00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:31.710
But either way, this A16 bionic here

00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:34.620
is more than good enough
in a phone of this price,

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:37.440
as far as performance and
handling everyday tasks

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:40.470
and gaming and flying
around iOS at 60 hertz.

00:06:40.470 --> 00:06:43.710
And the one thing you definitely
can argue for 60 hertz

00:06:43.710 --> 00:06:45.120
would be battery life,

00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:47.490
because despite all the
issues floating around,

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:49.680
the battery life on these
phones has been pretty good.

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:50.513
So I don't know if you saw it,

00:06:50.513 --> 00:06:52.530
but Apple has officially now addressed

00:06:52.530 --> 00:06:54.960
the heat and battery
issues that some people,

00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:58.230
including myself, have been
reporting with these iPhones.

00:06:58.230 --> 00:06:59.970
So an iOS update is coming

00:06:59.970 --> 00:07:02.100
and it seems like some
specific third party apps,

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:04.200
like Instagram, were also having issues

00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:06.090
and those should be getting updates too.

00:07:06.090 --> 00:07:08.970
But on average, the battery life on my 15

00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:11.933
has been better than my
battery on the 15 Pro.

00:07:11.933 --> 00:07:13.770
And the 15 Plus looks to have

00:07:13.770 --> 00:07:15.870
the best battery life ever on any iPhone,

00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:16.950
which is really promising.

00:07:16.950 --> 00:07:21.300
So that combination of the
A16 Bionic, which is not new,

00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:24.330
and 60 hertz screens, which are not new,

00:07:24.330 --> 00:07:25.620
are giving you great battery life.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:28.380
Also, USB-C is definitely not new

00:07:28.380 --> 00:07:31.590
but here it is alongside all
the benefits that come with it,

00:07:31.590 --> 00:07:34.260
from using the same cable
to charge everything,

00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:36.120
to plugging into more accessories,

00:07:36.120 --> 00:07:39.180
like monitors and keyboards
and all kinds of other stuff.

00:07:39.180 --> 00:07:41.610
It is sad that the older chip does mean

