are actually looking a little better,

00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:19.110
a little more detailed than
last year's Pro phones.

00:11:19.110 --> 00:11:21.000
And then, there's the new

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:24.330
auto-Portrait Mode detection
feature, which is pretty sweet.

00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:26.970
Basically you don't have
to switch to Portrait Mode

00:11:26.970 --> 00:11:30.090
to take a photo that captures
all of the depth information

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:32.940
that allows you to turn it into
a Portrait Mode photo later.

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:36.570
So as long as you're pointing
the camera at a human subject

00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:40.890
or a cat or a dog as identified
by the neural engine,

00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:44.490
or if you tap to focus, you
automatically get this little F

00:11:44.490 --> 00:11:45.780
at the bottom corner of the screen,

00:11:45.780 --> 00:11:47.340
which means it's capturing the data needed

00:11:47.340 --> 00:11:49.440
for Portrait Mode, just in case.

00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:51.060
And so, then, later, if you decide,

00:11:51.060 --> 00:11:53.400
eh, I actually do want this
to be a Portrait Mode shot,

00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:54.660
you go into your gallery

00:11:54.660 --> 00:11:57.000
and just make it a Portrait Mode photo,

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:59.460
that you can even then go
in and edit and play with.

00:11:59.460 --> 00:12:00.600
Some people have been describing it

00:12:00.600 --> 00:12:03.150
as being able to change
the focus point later.

00:12:03.150 --> 00:12:04.830
It's not exactly doing that,

00:12:04.830 --> 00:12:06.600
you can't like save something

00:12:06.600 --> 00:12:08.850
that was out of focus by bringing it back.

00:12:08.850 --> 00:12:10.770
But basically, for the classic iPhone shot

00:12:10.770 --> 00:12:13.320
where it kind of looks like
everything is in focus,

00:12:13.320 --> 00:12:14.805
then, yeah, you can
play with Portrait Mode

00:12:14.805 --> 00:12:16.440
and get really good results.

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:18.990
Last year's Pro iPhone has the same chip,

00:12:18.990 --> 00:12:21.270
also has a 48 megapixel main camera

00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:23.220
and has the same neural engine,

00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:25.978
doesn't get this feature, for some reason.

00:12:25.978 --> 00:12:27.150
Also kind of weird.

00:12:27.150 --> 00:12:28.710
So look, with these reviews,

00:12:28.710 --> 00:12:30.480
we always make a lot of judgements

00:12:30.480 --> 00:12:34.680
about what we think the
typical iPhone buyer is,

00:12:34.680 --> 00:12:37.530
what they actually care
about, what they'll notice,

00:12:37.530 --> 00:12:40.260
what they will appreciate
about a new phone.

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:43.500
And with this one, I do
feel like they've stacked up

00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:45.810
enough of these subtle improvements,

00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:47.190
that even though it looks the same

00:12:47.190 --> 00:12:50.280
and there's not really that
much that's actually new here,

00:12:50.280 --> 00:12:51.480
they've at least stacked enough things

00:12:51.480 --> 00:12:53.700
that it feels like an
appreciably better phone.

00:12:53.700 --> 00:12:56.700
So my verdict is, if
you have an iPhone 14,

00:12:56.700 --> 00:12:59.460
you don't have to upgrade,
of course, even a 13 maybe.

00:12:59.460 --> 00:13:01.050
But if you have an older phone

00:13:01.050 --> 00:13:02.790
and you're looking to
upgrade to a new iPhone,

00:13:02.790 --> 00:13:04.537
every year, I always
get friends asking like,

00:13:04.537 --> 00:13:07.110
"Oh, should I just get the older,

00:13:07.110 --> 00:13:09.780
like last year's iPhone
to save some money?"

00:13:09.780 --> 00:13:10.860
And no, I actually wouldn't,

00:13:10.860 --> 00:13:13.110
I would say just get the iPhone 15.

00:13:13.110 --> 00:13:14.250
There's enough new changes here,

00:13:14.250 --> 00:13:17.370
it's a better phone in
every way and it's also USB.

00:13:17.370 --> 00:13:19.470
Like, you don't buy a base iPhone

00:13:19.470 --> 00:13:21.210
to get the bleeding edge of tech,

00:13:21.210 --> 00:13:23.070
you buy it just 'cause
it works and it's fine

00:13:23.070 --> 00:13:25.298
and it's gonna be familiar and
work for the next few years.

00:13:25.298 --> 00:13:26.850
And just knowing that you're gonna have it

00:13:26.850 --> 00:13:27.683
for the next few years,

00:13:27.683 --> 00:13:29.670
I would not recommend
buying a Lightning iPhone

00:13:29.670 --> 00:13:32.130
as we just moved everything forward

00:13:32.130 --> 00:13:34.770
into the world of USB type C.

00:13:34.770 --> 00:13:36.900
Just get the new one, just
grab the boring new iPhone

00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:40.410
with nothing that's actually that new.

